The Herald Sports Reporter HARARE Athletic Board will on Saturday hold their track and field championships at the National Sports Stadium. The competition will take place at the B Arena and will cater for Under-14s, Under-16s, Under-18s, Under-20s and Seniors. For track events, participants will compete in 100m, 200m, 400m, 800m, 1 500m, 3 000m for women, 5 000m for men and 4x100m relay. Field events on offer include long jump, triple jump, high jump, shot put, discus and javelin. The provincial board said the meet is a platform to prepare for 2023 events which include local competitions such as NAPH and NASH championships, ZTISU Championships, national championships as well as regional and continental competitions.